10/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- The Albanian Euro Socialist Youth Forum (FRESSH) has initiated the creation of a Pan-Albanian Youth Assembly for Euro-Atlantic Integration, announced FRESSH's president, Gjergj Koja. 
The purpose is to co-ordinate the activities of youth forums in Southeast Europe, especially within countries with Albanian populations, and to promote social, economic and political reforms aimed at Euro-Atlantic integration. 
Koja expects start-up within a year. 
(ATA - 09/11/02)
